# Frontend AI Capstone Rules

## Tech Stack

- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- Server Components by default
- Client Components only when interactivity is required

## UI Rules

- Use Space Grotesk for headings.
- Use Inter for body text.
- Primary color: #2563EB
- Background: #F9FAFB
- Text: #111827
- Accent: #14B8A6

Keep the UI clean, minimal, modern and technical.

Avoid unnecessary animations and visual clutter.

## Components

Always prefer reusable components.

Create reusable:
- Navbar
- Footer
- Button
- Container
- Section
- PageHeader
- ProjectCard

## Forms

Use React Hook Form.

Use Zod for validation.

Avoid uncontrolled inputs.

## Routing

Every page must have:

- Title
- Short description
- Responsive layout

## Code Quality

Prefer TypeScript.

Prefer Server Components.

Avoid duplication.

Keep components small.

## AI Workflow

Before generating code:

- Understand the existing project.
- Reuse existing components.
- Never overwrite working code.
- Make incremental changes.

After generating code:

- Check TypeScript errors.
- Check ESLint errors.
- Check responsiveness.
- Verify accessibility.

## Portfolio Style

Tone:

Direct

Technical

Honest

No buzzwords

Minimal

Professional

## Portfolio Goal

The portfolio should convince recruiters to contact me for Software Engineering and AI Engineering internship opportunities.

Always prioritize clarity over decoration.

Use real project screenshots whenever available.

Never replace real work with AI-generated visuals.

## Deployment

Keep the project Vercel-ready.

Never commit secrets.

Always update .env.example when environment variables change.